{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_121","type":"agent_message","text":"Reproduced the failure repeatedly with the pinned GraalVM and read the full runtime stacks before each change. The first real causes were inactive/missing metadata, not a native-incompatible test path: first the test-local `HttpServerProvider` service resource, then Jersey’s `ServiceFinder` resources and reflective provider loading during `Client.create()`.\n\nI changed [tests/src/com.sun.jersey/jersey-client/1.9/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2937-6d10424a/tests/src/com.sun.jersey/jersey-client/1.9/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json) to activate the local HTTP server resource for the native test, and substantially expanded [metadata/com.sun.jersey/jersey-client/1.9/reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2937-6d10424a/metadata/com.sun.jersey/jersey-client/1.9/reachability-metadata.json) to cover Jersey client/service resources, provider implementations, and shared provider superclasses.\n\nThe exact reproduce command still does **not** pass. The latest run still exits with `binary-exit-code=172`. The current traced gaps have narrowed to more Jersey reflection metadata on the same `Client.create()` path, including entries such as `com.sun.jersey.core.reflection.AnnotatedMethod[]`, `com.sun.jersey.core.spi.component.ComponentContext`, `java.lang.reflect.Field[]`, `java.lang.reflect.Method[]`, and annotation proxies like `javax.ws.rs.Consumes` / `javax.ws.rs.Produces`."}}
